<style>
input[type=checkbox]:checked + a.strikethrough{
  text-decoration: line-through;
}
</style>
<div class="col-lg-12">
<h3>Games for Trade</h3>
<p>Among our large collection of Board Games, there are some we no longer spend our time playing.</p>
Although playing Table-Top Games is our <em>primary</em> leisure time activity, we simply suffer from "too many games, too little time".</p><p> In favor of others we like more or consider a more appropriate challenge, this list represents those we have decided (reluctantly) to <em>pass on</em> to another avid gamer.</p>
<p>If any of these interest you, click the checkbox on all you like then click <span id="trade-link">"Let's Barter"</span>.</p>
<p>We can negotiate a barter (that, I promise, will be favorable to you!).</p>
</div>

<div class="col-md-2"></div>
<div class="col-md-8">
<form id="trade" action="/games" method="POST">
	<input type="submit" class="btn btn-default" value="Let's Barter"></input>
<ul>
<% @games_list.each do |game| %>
  <li><div class="checkbox"><input name="<%= game[:name] %>" type="checkbox" <%= "checked=\"checked\"" unless game[:checked].nil? %> /><a class="strikethrough" href="<%= game[:url] %>" title="<%= game[:name] %>"><%= game[:name] %></a></li>
<% end %>
</ul>
</form>
</div>
<div class="col-md-2"></div>

